![](image)Macron celebrating France's victory over Croatia in the 2018 World Cup final in Moscow, Russia
A fan of football, Macron is a supporter of French club Olympique de Marseille.[346] During the 2018 World Cup, he attended the semi-final between France and Belgium with the Belgian King Philippe and Queen Mathilde,[347] and at the World Cup final against Croatia, he sat and celebrated alongside Croatian president Kolinda Grabar-Kitarović. Macron received widespread media attention for his celebrations and his interactions with the Croatian president.[348][349][350][351][352]


On 17 December 2020, Macron tested positive for COVID-19[353] leading to the cancellation of his scheduled trips for the following month, including a visit to Lebanon.[354]

chat_history.content:
Based on my research, here are the heads of government for each World Cup winning country at the time of their victory:

2022 (Argentina) - Alberto Fernández was President of Argentina
2018 (France) - Emmanuel Macron was President of France
2014 (Germany) - Angela Merkel was Chancellor of Germany
2010 (Spain) - José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero was Prime Minister of Spain
2006 (Italy) - Romano Prodi was Prime Minister of Italy

It's worth noting that in France, the President (Macron) is the head of state and head of government, while in Argentina, the President (Fernández) also serves both roles. In Germany, the Chancellor (Merkel) is the head of government, while in Spain and Italy, the Prime Minister (Zapatero and Prodi respectively) serves as head of government.
